# ── Environment variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, and set the same keys in the Vercel
# dashboard (Project → Settings → Environment Variables) for deploys.
# Everything here is PUBLIC (NEXT_PUBLIC_*) — no secrets in this project.

# Canonical site origin. Used for metadataBase, canonical URLs, the sitemap,
# robots.txt, and JSON-LD. Defaults to https://praduansaha.com when unset
# (see src/lib/site.ts), so it's optional in production if that domain is live.
# On Vercel you can point it at the deployment URL for preview builds, e.g.
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-project.vercel.app
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://praduansaha.com
